docs.abstract: Beneath the acrimony, two potential paths for China seem to be emerging in the trade war with the United States.

docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — The United States and China have sparred repeatedly over trade, in a tit-for-tat skirmish that has shown little sign of abating. High-level talks have stalled, while both sides have been threatening further tariffs in recent days.

docs.abstract: In a satirical new novel, a former Google executive identifies the technology industry’s chief issue: its narrow engineering-focused bubble.
docs.snippet: In a satirical new novel, a former Google executive identifies the technology industry’s chief issue: its narrow engineering-focused bubble.
docs.lead_paragraph: Not long ago, it was Jessica Powell’s job to defend Silicon Valley from those who would question its worldview. As the head of public relations at Google, she ran a sprawling team that sought to buff the search company’s image and to keep criticism of the world-dominating, do-everything tech behemoth to a minimum.

headline.main: Silicon Valley’s Keystone Problem: ‘A Monoculture of Thought’
headline.print_headline: Inside Silicon Valley’s Bubble: A Monotonous Monoculture
